In [[Sufism]], '''dhawq''' (tasting) is direct, first-hand experience.<ref>[[Ibn Arabi]]. ''The Meccan Revelations, Vol 1''. Pir Press, 1988, p. 343.</ref> It refers, principally, to the [[Gnosis]] of God which is achieved experientially, as a result of rigorous [[empiricism | empiric]] spiritual wayfaring.<ref>Ovidio Salazar, "Al-Ghazali: Alchemist of Happiness", Video Documentary.</ref> It plays an important role in the epistemology of [[Al-Ghazzali]], and is often expressed, to some extent, in teleological statements scattered throughout his works.

