'''Enrico di Robilant''' (1924 - 10 October 2012) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Philosophy|philosopher]] of law.<ref name="Côté2001">{{cite book|last=Côté|first=Pauline|title=Chercheurs de dieux dans l'espace public|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1rXrWVEHwosC&pg=PA80|accessdate=9 June 2011|date=1 January 2001|publisher=University of Ottawa Press|language=Italian|isbn=978-2-7603-0535-9|pages=80–}}</ref> He taught [[Jurisprudence|philosophy of law]] and [[political philosophy]] at the [[University of Turin]], where he had been a follower of [[Norberto Bobbio]].
He focused his attention on [[classical liberalism]], [[Canon Law]], [[Libertarianism|libertarian]] legal theory, and the relationship between [[Roman Catholic Church|Catholicism]] and Law.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Enrico Cassini|title=L’importanza di essere liberali. Enrico di Robilant|url=http://www.centroeinaudi.it/agenda-liberale/articoli/3754-l%E2%80%99importanza-di-essere-liberali-la-filosofia-di-enrico-di-robilant.html|website=centroeinaudi.it/|accessdate=4 February 2015|archivedate=19 February 2014|language=Italian}}</ref>

